Step 1 : Initiate a local kubernete environment - minikube

#What is minikube 
Minikube is a local Kubernetes environment that lets you run and test Kubernetes clusters right on your machine.


#Why Minikube Is Useful ?
Local Kubernetes Playground  that allows you to run single-node Kubernetes cluster on your laptop locally, with using any external tool.
Real Kubernetes Experience You get kubectl commands and YAML configurations you'd use in production. It is great for practicing pod/service readiness

#what if we don't run minikube ?
If you donâ€™t run Minikube or any other Kubernetes cluster, then kubectl has nowhere to send your commands.
Example : drive a car without an engine.



#Practical

- Here we are trying to run our first pod without activating the kubernetes environment i.e, MiniKube


/mnt/d/PROJECT/kubernetes_learning$ kubectl run nginx --image=nginx
E1031 20:29:12.042702    8184 memcache.go:265] "Unhandled Error" err="couldn't get current server API group list: Get \"http://localhost:8080/api?timeout=32s\": dial tcp 127.0.0.1:8080: connect: connection refused"
The connection to the server localhost:8080 was refused -  did you specify the right host or port?

Now lets start minikube and the run our first POD.
